WEBVTT

00:00.793 --> 00:02.685
<i>Previously on "Dark Matter"...</i>

00:02.710 --> 00:06.613
We wait, and try not to
get drawn into the conflict.

00:06.638 --> 00:08.571
And how long do you think that'll last?

00:09.040 --> 00:10.640
I don't believe it.

00:11.176 --> 00:12.886
Hello, pumpkin.

00:12.911 --> 00:14.826
You think she's the one
who had my friends killed

00:14.851 --> 00:15.755
over this?

00:15.780 --> 00:17.123
[both grunting, shouting]

00:17.148 --> 00:18.325
[shouts]

00:18.350 --> 00:19.726
<i>You swore an oath.</i>

00:19.751 --> 00:22.095
And the throne will still
be here once you're gone.

00:22.120 --> 00:23.463
And who will occupy it?

00:23.488 --> 00:25.632
- Did you debate my fate?
- We did.

00:25.657 --> 00:28.255
And what was the result?

00:30.169 --> 00:33.147
<i>[intense musical sting]</i>

00:33.172 --> 00:40.211
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:41.547 --> 00:43.191
I can't make this any easier for you.

00:43.216 --> 00:44.759
You think this is easy?

00:44.784 --> 00:46.794
I am a threat to your crew.

00:46.819 --> 00:48.863
You have no choice. As
their leader, you need to...

00:48.888 --> 00:50.921
Who the hell are you to
lecture me on leadership?

00:52.558 --> 00:54.369
You had command of an entire empire

00:54.394 --> 00:55.370
and you blew it.

00:55.395 --> 00:58.239
<i>[tense music]</i>

00:58.264 --> 01:00.375
You're right. I failed my people

01:00.400 --> 01:02.910
and now I have nothing.

01:02.935 --> 01:07.448
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:07.473 --> 01:10.574
I would do the same thing
if I was in your place.

01:13.479 --> 01:15.312
[inhales shakily]

01:20.520 --> 01:22.363
<i>- Two!</i>
- What?

01:22.388 --> 01:24.399
<i>Is Ryo still alive?</i>

01:24.424 --> 01:28.069
- Yes, but...
<i>- Don't kill him.</i>

01:28.094 --> 01:29.937
There's nothing more to talk about.

01:29.962 --> 01:31.244
<i>We need you on the bridge.</i>

01:31.269 --> 01:33.941
<i>We've received a subspace transmission.</i>

01:33.966 --> 01:35.199
From who?

01:37.303 --> 01:39.714
Put him on screen.

01:39.739 --> 01:41.516
Teku. I'm glad to see

01:41.541 --> 01:42.717
you made it out alive.

01:42.742 --> 01:44.519
<i>The feeling's mutual.</i>

01:44.544 --> 01:46.754
<i>Can I also assume that Ryo made it out?</i>

01:46.779 --> 01:49.190
Yes, I kept up my end of our deal.

01:49.215 --> 01:52.527
- He's onboard.
- <i>We need to discuss his return.</i>

01:52.552 --> 01:54.929
I said I'd get him off
the planet, and I did.

01:54.954 --> 01:56.637
I didn't promise anything after that.

01:56.662 --> 02:00.601
<i>You should know that I did
not leave Zairon empty-handed.</i>

02:00.626 --> 02:02.737
<i>I am, in fact, in command of a fleet</i>

02:02.762 --> 02:05.239
<i>of ships that remain
loyal to the Emperor.</i>

02:05.264 --> 02:07.031
He's not Emperor anymore.

02:08.568 --> 02:12.213
<i>He is the rightful heir of Ishida.</i>

02:12.238 --> 02:14.715
<i>And we want him back.</i>

02:14.740 --> 02:17.718
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

02:17.743 --> 02:20.321
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:20.346 --> 02:22.323
<i>[energy surging]</i>

02:22.348 --> 02:24.528
<i>[rock music]</i>

02:24.553 --> 02:30.350
- <font color="#D81D1D">Synced and corrected by VitoSilans</font> -
Resync by emeline-whovian
-- <font color="#138CE9">www.Addic7ed.com</fon

02:31.324 --> 02:34.001
Just out of curiosity,

02:34.026 --> 02:35.670
when you say "fleet,"

02:35.695 --> 02:38.139
how many ships are we
talking about, here?

02:38.164 --> 02:41.142
<i>Six cruisers, three destroyers.</i>

02:41.167 --> 02:42.743
All with nowhere to go.

02:42.768 --> 02:44.345
- No direction.
- <i>It's true,</i>

02:44.370 --> 02:46.314
<i>we are homeless and without allies,</i>

02:46.339 --> 02:48.916
<i>but we are united behind one purpose:</i>

02:48.941 --> 02:51.319
<i>to restore our emperor
to his rightful place.</i>

02:51.344 --> 02:52.620
It's not that simple.

02:52.645 --> 02:54.477
He has things to answer for.

02:54.502 --> 02:56.290
<i>He's a tyrant, a mass murderer...</i>

02:56.315 --> 02:58.893
A ruler who had to make hard decisions.

02:58.918 --> 03:01.162
He attacked us, stole from us,

03:01.187 --> 03:03.131
and more importantly, he
bears some responsibility

03:03.156 --> 03:04.565
for the death of our friend.

03:04.590 --> 03:05.933
And not to make this all about me,

03:05.958 --> 03:07.401
but he also sent an assassin

03:07.426 --> 03:09.270
who tried to kill me... Repeatedly.

03:09.295 --> 03:11.672
I know there is bad blood between you,

03:11.697 --> 03:14.275
and I know that nothing pained him more.

03:14.300 --> 03:15.659
He tell you that himself?

03:15.684 --> 03:17.678
<i>Ryo was raised to never show weakness.</i>

03:17.703 --> 03:19.714
<i>But I know for a fact</i>

03:19.739 --> 03:21.349
<i>that he was heartbroken.</i>

03:21.374 --> 03:23.017
That's assuming he has one.

03:23.042 --> 03:24.619
<i>I do not want us to be enemies.</i>

03:24.644 --> 03:26.386
<i>So, as a show of good faith,</i>

03:26.411 --> 03:29.457
- <i>I have something to offer you.</i>
- What are you talking about?

03:29.482 --> 03:31.025
<i>It concerns the man who kidnapped you</i>

03:31.050 --> 03:32.360
<i>and brought you to Zairon.</i>

03:32.385 --> 03:33.794
You mean Boone?

03:33.819 --> 03:35.496
<i>I sensed he was untrustworthy,</i>

03:35.521 --> 03:38.833
<i>so I placed a tracking
device on his ship...</i>

03:38.858 --> 03:40.157
<i>As a precaution.</i>

03:42.695 --> 03:44.138
<i>I know where he went.</i>

03:44.163 --> 03:47.141
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

03:47.166 --> 03:49.410
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:49.435 --> 03:51.379
The coordinates that Teku provided

03:51.404 --> 03:53.481
are deep within an uninhabited system.

03:53.506 --> 03:56.884
It would appear their Marauder
has not moved in some time.

03:56.909 --> 03:59.487
Off-grid. Some kind of hideout.

03:59.512 --> 04:01.389
Or it's the place the
Ishida fleet's waiting

04:01.414 --> 04:03.157
to get the jump on us
the second we drop out.

04:03.182 --> 04:05.293
I don't think Teku would do that.

04:05.318 --> 04:06.961
'Cause you know him so well?

04:06.986 --> 04:10.087
I saw what kind of man
he was in Four's memories.

04:11.624 --> 04:13.334
People change.

04:13.359 --> 04:15.102
You've gotta be at
least a little curious.

04:15.127 --> 04:16.771
- Nope.
- I'm not the one

04:16.796 --> 04:18.380
with a double out there ruining my rep.

04:18.406 --> 04:20.875
Listen, I appreciate you
insinuating that I have a rep

04:20.899 --> 04:23.110
worth protecting, but I think it's crazy

04:23.135 --> 04:24.912
that we're blindly trusting this guy.

04:24.937 --> 04:26.347
The fact that there is another you

04:26.372 --> 04:28.715
and another me out there is a problem.

04:28.740 --> 04:30.585
We always knew we were
gonna have to deal with this

04:30.610 --> 04:32.720
sooner or later.

04:32.745 --> 04:34.989
What if he's lying? Hmm?

04:35.014 --> 04:36.791
<i>[dark music]</i>

04:36.816 --> 04:38.693
<i>So, is this a stay of execution?</i>

04:38.718 --> 04:40.895
It's a temporary one.

04:40.920 --> 04:43.231
I can assure you that's not necessary.

04:43.256 --> 04:44.799
I won't attempt to escape.

04:44.824 --> 04:47.134
The simple fact is I have nowhere to go.

04:47.159 --> 04:50.194
[beeping, door whooshing open]

04:59.672 --> 05:01.082
I thought you might wanna know...

05:01.107 --> 05:05.386
I spoke to Teku. He made it out alive.

05:05.411 --> 05:08.556
I'm glad. I was worried about him.

05:08.581 --> 05:10.625
He's important to you.

05:10.650 --> 05:12.827
Very much so.

05:12.852 --> 05:15.263
Why?

05:15.288 --> 05:17.421
Because he's always been a good friend.

05:18.624 --> 05:21.135
When I returned to Zairon,
I knew he was the one

05:21.160 --> 05:22.803
I could trust above all others.

05:22.828 --> 05:24.762
He's the most honorable man I know.

05:26.532 --> 05:29.333
Well, let's hope you're right.

05:32.104 --> 05:37.151
<i>♪ ♪</i>

05:37.176 --> 05:38.586
I still don't like it.

05:38.611 --> 05:40.154
I don't entirely disagree with you,

05:40.179 --> 05:41.931
but I still think it's
worth investigating.

05:41.956 --> 05:44.091
We'll have the Android
drop us out just short

05:44.116 --> 05:46.060
of the coordinates and
use long-range sensors

05:46.085 --> 05:48.129
to see what's waiting
for us. Good enough?

05:48.154 --> 05:50.831
Do I have a choice?

05:50.856 --> 05:53.301
Fine.

05:53.326 --> 05:55.359
[energy surging]

06:02.001 --> 06:04.278
[control panel beeping]

06:04.303 --> 06:06.236
- Come in.
- [door whooshes open]

06:08.140 --> 06:09.884
- Hey.
- Hey.

06:09.909 --> 06:11.419
I'm not interrupting anything, am I?

06:11.444 --> 06:13.010
No, no, it's fine.

06:17.583 --> 06:19.237
Are you all right?

06:19.262 --> 06:20.540
Of course. What do you mean?

06:20.565 --> 06:21.758
I don't know. It's just that,

06:21.783 --> 06:23.728
since we've got back from Zairon,

06:23.753 --> 06:25.599
I get the feeling
something's bothering you.

06:25.624 --> 06:28.135
[scoffs] You mean besides the fact

06:28.160 --> 06:31.639
that Two, Three, and the
Android all voted to kill Four?

06:31.664 --> 06:33.364
You mean Ryo.

06:35.167 --> 06:36.777
[sighs]

06:36.802 --> 06:38.846
Hey, if you don't wanna talk about it...

06:38.871 --> 06:41.482
No. No, it's fine.

06:41.507 --> 06:45.853
You were gonna find out
sooner or later anyway.

06:45.878 --> 06:48.322
It wasn't a coincidence.

06:48.347 --> 06:50.024
- What wasn't?
- The bearded man...

06:50.049 --> 06:52.727
The one I took the Blink Drive from.

06:52.752 --> 06:55.329
It was no accident that
he was on Eridani-6.

06:55.354 --> 06:57.221
What are you talking about?

06:59.191 --> 07:03.204
I was looking for my sister.

07:03.229 --> 07:06.006
She was adopted by a wealthy family

07:06.031 --> 07:08.876
when I was just a baby.
Somehow I must have found her

07:08.901 --> 07:11.812
and made contact, because I invited her

07:11.837 --> 07:14.248
to meet me on the station.

07:14.273 --> 07:16.650
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:16.675 --> 07:19.009
Only she didn't come alone.

07:21.580 --> 07:24.014
She came with her mother.

07:28.687 --> 07:30.898
Alicia Reynaud.

07:30.923 --> 07:33.868
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

07:33.893 --> 07:36.937
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:36.962 --> 07:39.963
[thudding]

07:43.936 --> 07:45.746
[panting]

07:45.771 --> 07:47.581
Physical exertion is an excellent means

07:47.606 --> 07:49.417
of stress reduction.

07:49.442 --> 07:53.220
[grunting]

07:53.245 --> 07:55.756
Are you feeling more relaxed?

07:55.781 --> 07:57.799
- Not really.
- Then you might want

07:57.824 --> 08:00.528
to consider alternate
dynamic activities:

08:00.553 --> 08:04.031
running, weight lifting...

08:04.056 --> 08:06.434
- sexual congress.
- Yup, yup.

08:06.459 --> 08:08.640
Okay. [exhales]

08:08.665 --> 08:11.302
I will keep that... in mind.

08:12.898 --> 08:14.708
- What do you got?
- I was able to get into

08:14.733 --> 08:17.311
the lockbox... The one
matching the description

08:17.336 --> 08:19.447
that Ryo gave you.

08:19.472 --> 08:22.082
I found this.

08:22.107 --> 08:25.319
A data storage device. It's
like the one he mentioned.

08:25.344 --> 08:26.887
The files are pass-locked.

08:26.912 --> 08:28.622
I've been unable to read them,

08:28.647 --> 08:31.892
but this one caught my eye.

08:31.917 --> 08:34.294
It's labeled "Kryden."

08:34.320 --> 08:36.263
<i>[mysterious music]</i>

08:36.288 --> 08:43.227
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:50.903 --> 08:53.881
<i>[gentle music]</i>

08:53.906 --> 09:01.011
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:13.893 --> 09:16.470
<i>[musical sting]</i>

09:16.495 --> 09:19.473
<i>[somber music]</i>

09:19.498 --> 09:23.077
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:23.102 --> 09:25.235
[mind-link devices beep]

09:27.873 --> 09:29.383
[sighs]

09:29.408 --> 09:36.446
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:42.221 --> 09:45.533
<i>Three, where are you?</i>

09:45.558 --> 09:47.067
Infirmary.

09:47.092 --> 09:48.625
<i>Are you all right?</i>

09:53.198 --> 09:54.631
Yeah. Yeah, I'm okay.

09:54.656 --> 09:56.167
<i>Well, you might want to get up here.</i>

09:56.192 --> 09:59.180
- <i>We're about to drop out.</i>
- On my way.

09:59.205 --> 10:02.240
[energy surging]

10:05.578 --> 10:07.821
- Any sign of ships?
- Not yet.

10:07.846 --> 10:09.356
However, I am detecting something

10:09.381 --> 10:11.025
at the coordinates Teku provided...

10:11.050 --> 10:12.651
Something quite large.

10:12.676 --> 10:14.361
Are we close enough to get a visual?

10:14.386 --> 10:16.063
Yes. Onscreen.

10:16.088 --> 10:17.898
[screen beeps]

10:17.923 --> 10:19.700
<i>[mysterious music]</i>

10:19.725 --> 10:22.269
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:22.294 --> 10:23.627
Magnify.

10:30.603 --> 10:32.913
Is that what I think it is?

10:32.938 --> 10:34.782
That's Project Phoenix,

10:34.807 --> 10:36.617
Ferrous' secret shipyard...

10:36.642 --> 10:38.118
The real one this time.

10:38.143 --> 10:41.878
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

10:45.717 --> 10:49.096
Son of a bitch... Boone and his
crew are working for Ferrous now?

10:49.121 --> 10:51.459
- How'd they swing that?
- We've got bigger worries.

10:51.485 --> 10:53.208
Those ships look
like they're almost finished.

10:53.234 --> 10:55.262
And if they launch,
Ferrous will be unstoppable.

10:55.288 --> 10:56.779
Then let's make sure
that doesn't happen.

10:56.805 --> 10:57.758
You wanna attack them?

10:57.783 --> 10:58.976
We have to do something.

10:59.001 --> 11:00.848
Look, kid, I'm all
for saving the galaxy,

11:00.873 --> 11:02.356
but we're one ship, and they're lots,

11:02.381 --> 11:04.558
and... lots and lots of ships.

11:04.982 --> 11:05.968
Have they spotted us?

11:05.994 --> 11:07.626
This far out, it's unlikely.

11:07.652 --> 11:08.867
Element of surprise.

11:08.893 --> 11:10.735
However, there is a problem.

11:10.956 --> 11:14.268
I'm detecting the leading edge
of an Aslanov Exclusion Field,

11:14.293 --> 11:16.403
- dead ahead.
- Aw, shit.

11:16.428 --> 11:17.993
You were right to be cautious.

11:18.363 --> 11:20.140
Any closer, and we
would've hit the field.

11:20.165 --> 11:22.743
Our FTL would have failed,
and we most definitely

11:22.768 --> 11:24.144
would have been detected.

11:24.169 --> 11:25.612
How long to get there in sublight?

11:25.637 --> 11:27.948
- 2 1/2 hours.
- They'd detect us

11:27.973 --> 11:29.816
before we could get anywhere near it.

11:29.841 --> 11:32.085
- We could blink in.
- I don't know.

11:32.110 --> 11:33.787
Three's right. One ship against

11:33.812 --> 11:35.923
something that big? We
don't have the firepower.

11:35.948 --> 11:38.325
We don't even know what
kind of defenses they have.

11:38.350 --> 11:40.594
Look, I don't want those ships to launch

11:40.619 --> 11:42.729
any more than you do,
but I think we could use

11:42.754 --> 11:44.598
a little help on this one.

11:44.623 --> 11:46.500
Who?

11:46.525 --> 11:48.368
Mikkei's been trying
to stay out of the war

11:48.393 --> 11:49.592
as best they can.

11:49.617 --> 11:52.184
Maybe it's time they
got their hands dirty.

11:53.165 --> 11:56.199
[engines roaring]

12:01.873 --> 12:04.451
It's Commander Truffault.

12:04.476 --> 12:06.820
- Commander.
<i>- Hello again, "Raza."</i>

12:06.845 --> 12:08.989
Did you get a chance to look
at those images we sent you?

12:09.014 --> 12:10.457
<i>Yes. They corroborate</i>

12:10.482 --> 12:11.925
- <i>our recent intel.</i>
- Oh.

12:11.950 --> 12:13.660
You already knew about the shipyard.

12:13.685 --> 12:15.429
<i>We have an agent inside Ferrous Corp</i>

12:15.454 --> 12:17.564
<i>who tipped us off, but we weren't sure</i>

12:17.589 --> 12:19.333
<i>whether our source was wholly reliable.</i>

12:19.358 --> 12:21.668
Well, I'd say those images confirm it.

12:21.693 --> 12:24.104
<i>Yes... we need to take out</i>

12:24.129 --> 12:26.640
<i>that shipyard, which is where you</i>

12:26.665 --> 12:28.608
- <i>and your ship come in.</i>
- Oh?

12:28.633 --> 12:31.111
<i>With your Blink Drive operational,</i>

12:31.136 --> 12:32.879
<i>you have the only ship in the galaxy</i>

12:32.904 --> 12:35.115
<i>that can get past that exclusion field.</i>

12:35.140 --> 12:37.784
<i>So, I'd like to offer the services</i>

12:37.809 --> 12:39.786
<i>of Mikkei's finest scientists</i>

12:39.811 --> 12:41.888
<i>to take a look at your damaged drive.</i>

12:41.913 --> 12:44.647
Well, we fixed it. It's already working.

12:46.818 --> 12:50.330
<i>Well, well, well. What
a pleasant surprise.</i>

12:50.355 --> 12:52.432
<i>In that case, I would very much like</i>

12:52.457 --> 12:55.602
<i>to come over and discuss
a proposal with you.</i>

12:55.627 --> 12:57.004
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

12:57.029 --> 12:59.295
[energy surging]

13:07.696 --> 13:09.474
That thing full of money?

13:09.499 --> 13:11.900
We haven't reached the
payment stage quite yet.

13:13.945 --> 13:17.190
- What the hell?
- That looks familiar.

13:17.215 --> 13:19.693
It should.

13:19.718 --> 13:22.295
It's a white-hole device,
courtesy of our friends

13:22.320 --> 13:26.967
at Traugott... one of only
two prototypes ever completed.

13:26.992 --> 13:29.703
Yeah, we remember what
happened to the other one.

13:29.728 --> 13:32.539
Circumstances have changed since then.

13:32.564 --> 13:35.675
Our relationship with
Traugott has evolved.

13:35.700 --> 13:37.044
So, you're allies now?

13:37.069 --> 13:39.179
Not officially, but we have been

13:39.204 --> 13:41.615
discreetly supplying them with weapons

13:41.640 --> 13:43.383
and other resources for quite some time.

13:43.408 --> 13:45.452
Yeah, they tried to kill us in prison.

13:45.477 --> 13:48.021
That was before the war. And anyway,

13:48.046 --> 13:49.723
you of all people
should know not to take

13:49.748 --> 13:51.625
that sort of thing personally.

13:51.650 --> 13:53.608
I don't know. Attacking and taking out

13:53.633 --> 13:55.929
those ships is one thing, but
destroying that entire structure

13:55.954 --> 13:57.264
with all those people onboard?

13:57.289 --> 13:58.832
We have no other option.

13:58.857 --> 14:01.401
This is our one and only shot.

14:01.426 --> 14:04.237
Look, Ferrous is winning the war,

14:04.262 --> 14:06.173
but they have stretched their resources

14:06.198 --> 14:08.842
to the breaking point.
And that was their plan

14:08.867 --> 14:11.144
from the very beginning,
because they are counting on

14:11.169 --> 14:14.681
those ships coming
online at the key moment.

14:14.706 --> 14:17.184
Prevent that from happening,
and their strategy collapses.

14:17.209 --> 14:19.553
They'll be caught in a protracted

14:19.578 --> 14:24.658
war of attrition they can't win,
against half a dozen enemies.

14:24.683 --> 14:27.027
When all sides are exhausted...

14:27.052 --> 14:28.390
Mikkei steps in,

14:28.415 --> 14:31.131
the most powerful
corporation in the galaxy.

14:31.156 --> 14:34.983
And your most grateful ally.

14:38.996 --> 14:41.773
Well... we don't have to risk the ship.

14:41.798 --> 14:43.977
We could hook up the Blink
Drive to the Marauder.

14:44.002 --> 14:46.012
They'd never even know we were there.

14:46.037 --> 14:47.747
When you say "grateful," what kind

14:47.772 --> 14:49.182
of gratitude are we talking about, here?

14:49.207 --> 14:50.383
More money than you could spend

14:50.408 --> 14:51.751
in your lifetime.

14:51.776 --> 14:52.986
- Hmm.
- And for those of you

14:53.011 --> 14:55.388
who need other motivation,

14:55.413 --> 14:59.793
if you don't do this
and those ships launch,

14:59.818 --> 15:02.552
Ferrous runs the table.

15:04.389 --> 15:06.199
<i>Android, we need you to prep</i>

15:06.224 --> 15:08.301
<i>the Marauder for Blink Drive operation.</i>

15:08.326 --> 15:09.503
<i>We're going back.</i>

15:09.528 --> 15:11.171
Understood.

15:11.196 --> 15:14.141
<i>[intense music]</i>

15:14.166 --> 15:18.712
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:18.737 --> 15:20.413
- What are you doing?
- Coming with.

15:20.438 --> 15:22.149
Well, that's not
necessary. We're not even

15:22.174 --> 15:25.018
- boarding the facility.
- Better safe than sorry.

15:25.043 --> 15:32.058
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:32.083 --> 15:33.750
<i>All right, "Raza." Here we go.</i>

15:36.929 --> 15:43.967
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:53.438 --> 15:56.372
Aw, damn, that thing's big.

16:00.538 --> 16:02.182
[white-hole device beeping]

16:02.207 --> 16:04.085
I'm gonna set the timer for one minute.

16:04.110 --> 16:06.059
That should give us enough
time to jettison the bomb

16:06.084 --> 16:07.460
and get the hell out of here.

16:07.485 --> 16:09.829
[device whirring]

16:09.854 --> 16:12.799
[control panel beeping]

16:12.824 --> 16:14.524
All right, opening rear door.

16:20.765 --> 16:23.233
All right, that's it. Time to go.

16:25.604 --> 16:26.780
Engaging Blink Drive.

16:26.805 --> 16:29.282
[engine whirs]

16:29.307 --> 16:31.051
[frantic beeping]

16:31.076 --> 16:32.875
- What happened?
- Try again?

16:37.262 --> 16:39.159
- [engine whirs]
- What the hell's going on?

16:39.184 --> 16:41.127
Diagnostics are all in the green.

16:41.152 --> 16:42.929
Blink Drive is fully operational.

16:42.954 --> 16:44.731
- Then why are we still here?
- I don't know.

16:44.756 --> 16:46.146
15 seconds.

16:46.171 --> 16:48.034
- You can disarm that, right?
- No, I can't.

16:48.059 --> 16:49.537
Get us out of here, maximum sublight.

16:49.562 --> 16:51.404
It wouldn't do any good.
We don't have enough time

16:51.429 --> 16:53.607
to clear the blast radius.

16:53.632 --> 16:56.666
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

17:01.015 --> 17:04.943
<i>[ominous musical sting]</i>

17:04.968 --> 17:07.665
- What the hell?
- Why didn't it go off?

17:08.137 --> 17:09.213
[whooshing]

17:09.238 --> 17:11.372
[explosion, all shouting]

17:14.160 --> 17:15.703
All right. Station defenses.

17:15.728 --> 17:17.166
They're shooting at us.

17:17.313 --> 17:19.190
- We're getting a signal.
<i>- Marauder,</i>

17:19.214 --> 17:21.059
<i>we're locked in on your position.</i>

17:21.084 --> 17:23.362
<i>Try to run, and we'll
blow you out of space.</i>

17:32.729 --> 17:34.339
They should've been back by now.

17:34.364 --> 17:36.374
And that shipyard
should've been destroyed.

17:36.399 --> 17:39.511
- Something's wrong.
- You can say that again.

17:39.536 --> 17:41.179
It was a double cross.

17:41.204 --> 17:43.114
Traugott just launched multiple attacks

17:43.139 --> 17:45.565
against Mikkei's
holdings in three sectors.

17:45.590 --> 17:47.652
- What are you talking about?
- They obviously cut

17:47.677 --> 17:49.521
their own deal with Ferrous, which means

17:49.546 --> 17:51.156
they probably warned
them we were coming.

17:51.181 --> 17:53.057
This whole thing has been a setup.

17:53.082 --> 17:54.993
What does that mean?
They trapped the Marauder?

17:55.018 --> 17:56.795
- How is that possible?
- I don't know.

17:56.820 --> 17:58.758
- What about the bomb?
- My guess is

17:58.783 --> 18:00.799
they somehow tampered with it.

18:00.824 --> 18:02.937
I'm sorry. You're sorry?!

18:02.962 --> 18:04.906
- Are you kidding me?
- It is what it is.

18:04.931 --> 18:07.263
Now, our agent inside Ferrous
may still be able to help,

18:07.288 --> 18:10.175
but in the meantime, my
ships are needed elsewhere,

18:10.200 --> 18:12.477
and since this location
has been compromised,

18:12.502 --> 18:14.779
I would advise you leave as well.

18:14.804 --> 18:17.315
This is the rendezvous point.
We're not going anywhere.

18:17.340 --> 18:19.517
<i>[tense music]</i>

18:19.542 --> 18:21.953
Very well.

18:21.978 --> 18:23.871
I wish you good luck!

18:35.158 --> 18:37.635
Those two in there. You're with me.

18:37.660 --> 18:40.705
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

18:40.730 --> 18:47.768
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:50.039 --> 18:51.616
You know, I really can't help but think

18:51.641 --> 18:53.551
that I didn't need
to be on this mission.

18:53.576 --> 18:55.186
That's what we tried to tell you.

18:55.211 --> 18:56.827
Next time, be more persistent.

19:06.731 --> 19:09.132
Oh, good. Now we can get to work.

19:11.861 --> 19:13.505
I need you to tell
me everything you know

19:13.530 --> 19:15.673
- about the drive.
- I'm afraid that's not much.

19:15.698 --> 19:17.542
You adapted it to your
shuttle's sublight engines.

19:17.567 --> 19:19.477
- That took some doing.
- That was my Android.

19:19.502 --> 19:21.112
We could call her, if you like.

19:21.137 --> 19:22.580
That won't be necessary.

19:22.605 --> 19:24.015
You can leave us now.

19:24.040 --> 19:25.183
She's dangerous.

19:25.208 --> 19:27.452
I said you can leave.

19:27.477 --> 19:28.843
[sighs]

19:38.187 --> 19:40.532
Look, I'm not trying to play you.

19:40.557 --> 19:42.233
I really don't know
how that thing works.

19:42.258 --> 19:44.502
I've got nothing to offer.

19:44.527 --> 19:46.871
You can offer more than you know.

19:46.896 --> 19:48.606
And you will.

19:48.631 --> 19:52.466
<i>[dark, building music]</i>

19:54.704 --> 19:57.549
Good news. I brought a friend.

19:57.574 --> 19:59.183
Gentlemen!

19:59.208 --> 20:01.019
We have got to stop meeting like this.

20:01.044 --> 20:03.054
- Wexler.
- We should've killed you

20:03.079 --> 20:05.156
- when we had the chance.
- Ah, don't beat yourself up

20:05.181 --> 20:07.559
- over it, eh?
- Don't... touch me.

20:07.584 --> 20:09.794
- Where's the rest of your crew?
- Who, Portia and Tash?

20:09.819 --> 20:11.563
Getting their nails
done? What do I care?

20:11.588 --> 20:13.798
Android's back on the
ship. Boone's on a bender.

20:13.823 --> 20:15.600
He was staking out the
Nova system for a few weeks

20:15.625 --> 20:17.635
before you all showed up. I
think he went a little wiggy.

20:17.660 --> 20:19.103
Can we cut to the chase?

20:19.128 --> 20:20.538
Commander Nieman will be here soon.

20:20.563 --> 20:22.848
That's right! Your old pal.

20:22.873 --> 20:24.584
See, the thing is, he's got you guys

20:24.609 --> 20:26.277
and the Blink Drive, and for most men,

20:26.302 --> 20:28.279
that would be enough.
But, as we all know,

20:28.304 --> 20:30.181
Nieman is not most men.

20:30.206 --> 20:32.083
He wants his victory to be complete.

20:32.108 --> 20:33.551
He wants the "Raza."

20:33.576 --> 20:35.553
Admittedly, it's not nearly as valuable

20:35.578 --> 20:37.055
with just a glitchy Android

20:37.080 --> 20:38.823
and some green-haired
little girl onboard,

20:38.848 --> 20:40.658
but hey, what are you gonna do?

20:40.683 --> 20:43.294
First one to give up the
ship's location gets to live.

20:43.319 --> 20:45.096
[snorts]

20:45.121 --> 20:47.699
- Fine.
- Whoa.

20:47.724 --> 20:49.434
What, are you just gonna
take 'em out, just like that?

20:49.459 --> 20:50.547
If I kill this one,

20:50.572 --> 20:52.503
the other one will know I mean business.

20:52.528 --> 20:54.128
Well, yeah, but...

20:56.090 --> 20:57.809
don't you wanna soften
them up a bit first?

20:57.834 --> 20:59.043
I mean, that's half the fun, right?

20:59.068 --> 21:01.646
This way's easier.

21:01.671 --> 21:03.748
Okay. If you say so.

21:03.773 --> 21:04.805
[gun fires]

21:08.945 --> 21:12.256
He's right. That was easy.

21:12.281 --> 21:14.759
Oh, don't look so surprised.

21:14.784 --> 21:17.261
Truffault sends her regards, by the way.

21:17.286 --> 21:20.264
- You're her agent?
- Yeah, that's right.

21:20.289 --> 21:22.500
I got tired of taking
a backseat to Portia,

21:22.525 --> 21:25.803
so I cut my own side
deal. Seize the day.

21:25.828 --> 21:27.038
"Carpet" diem.

21:27.063 --> 21:28.272
Besides, Mikkei's got dental,

21:28.297 --> 21:29.440
so... whoa.

21:29.465 --> 21:31.509
You expect us to trust you?

21:31.534 --> 21:34.278
[sighs] No. I do expect you not to be

21:34.303 --> 21:36.381
- incredibly stupid, though.
- Yeah?

21:36.406 --> 21:37.786
They adapted the exclusion field.

21:37.811 --> 21:39.455
That's why you couldn't
blink out of here.

21:39.480 --> 21:40.911
They let you in the front door, and then

21:40.936 --> 21:42.627
- they locked it behind you.
- How the hell

21:42.652 --> 21:44.129
- did they manage that?
- They had a little help.

21:44.154 --> 21:45.857
I don't know. Our Android knows

21:45.882 --> 21:47.325
a thing or two about Blink Drives.

21:47.350 --> 21:49.761
Who let them know we were coming, hmm?

21:49.786 --> 21:51.496
You?

21:51.521 --> 21:53.097
Traugott sold you out.

21:53.122 --> 21:55.533
The bomb was a dud.

21:55.558 --> 21:57.669
Look, the only way
you're getting out of here

21:57.694 --> 22:00.038
is if you take down that
field. And I'm pretty sure

22:00.063 --> 22:01.406
there's only one person in this room

22:01.431 --> 22:03.608
who knows where the control room is.

22:03.633 --> 22:07.068
- [growls]
- [stammers nervously]

22:16.379 --> 22:18.389
[quietly] All right, around
this corner make a left

22:18.414 --> 22:19.924
and a right, and then all the way

22:19.949 --> 22:21.359
to the end, and you'll find the lab

22:21.384 --> 22:22.910
where they're holding your friend.

22:24.554 --> 22:26.297
I'll deal with the
exclusion field, and then

22:26.322 --> 22:27.999
we'll all meet up back
at the Marauder, okay?

22:28.024 --> 22:29.911
Break.

22:29.936 --> 22:31.129
Fat chance.

22:31.154 --> 22:33.438
I'm not letting you out of my sight.

22:33.463 --> 22:35.506
- Got this?
- I got it.

22:35.531 --> 22:38.377
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:38.402 --> 22:41.169
- Who hurt you?
- [sighs] Let's go.

22:45.742 --> 22:46.918
What are you doing here?

22:46.943 --> 22:49.253
I think he has authorization.

22:49.278 --> 22:52.557
- [gunshot]
- [groans]

22:52.582 --> 22:55.593
Oof. That stain's not coming out.

22:55.618 --> 22:56.828
Ah... Sure you know how

22:56.853 --> 22:59.163
to work this thing?

22:59.188 --> 23:01.099
Now, we can't just shut the system down.

23:01.124 --> 23:03.735
We need the station commander's
access code for that.

23:03.760 --> 23:05.737
But we could boost the signal enough

23:05.762 --> 23:07.206
to create a feedback loop.

23:07.231 --> 23:08.388
It'll cause a chain reaction

23:08.413 --> 23:12.110
that should fry the
entire satellite network.

23:12.135 --> 23:14.712
Beauty and brains.

23:14.737 --> 23:15.947
Just get to work.

23:15.972 --> 23:17.071
[clicks tongue]

23:21.744 --> 23:24.088
- Two, you okay?
- Yeah.

23:24.113 --> 23:26.657
- What happened?
- They were asking questions.

23:26.682 --> 23:28.226
I didn't have the answers.

23:28.251 --> 23:31.395
<i>[ominous music]</i>

23:31.420 --> 23:34.332
<i>♪ ♪</i>

23:34.357 --> 23:36.367
Who gave us the
location of the shipyard?

23:36.392 --> 23:37.969
- What?
- Earlier today,

23:37.994 --> 23:39.704
someone tipped us off to this location.

23:39.729 --> 23:41.672
Who was it?

23:41.697 --> 23:43.264
Teku.

23:45.004 --> 23:46.834
Just wanted to make
sure I wasn't bringing

23:46.859 --> 23:49.680
Portia Lin back on the ship with us.

23:49.705 --> 23:53.317
All right, let's go.

23:53.342 --> 23:55.019
And here. We. Go.

23:55.044 --> 23:58.122
[computer beeping quickly]

23:58.147 --> 24:01.192
<i>♪ ♪</i>

24:01.217 --> 24:04.579
Well, well, well. It's working.

24:04.604 --> 24:06.798
Now we got about five
minutes before they realize

24:06.823 --> 24:08.743
something's gone wrong
and sound a general alarm.

24:13.154 --> 24:16.140
<i>[tense music]</i>

24:16.165 --> 24:19.010
<i>♪ ♪</i>

24:19.035 --> 24:20.945
So, I trust that once we're out of here,

24:20.970 --> 24:23.014
you'll show your appreciation
in a very generous way.

24:23.039 --> 24:24.715
What happened to five minutes?

24:24.740 --> 24:26.580
- Slight miscalculation.
- [shouts]

24:26.605 --> 24:28.105
Oh, shit!

24:32.815 --> 24:34.381
[shouts]

24:38.721 --> 24:39.797
[whispering] Wexler?

24:39.822 --> 24:41.065
[alarm blaring]

24:41.090 --> 24:42.934
Wexler?!

24:42.959 --> 24:44.992
[huffs]

24:46.596 --> 24:49.173
You greasy little rat.

24:49.198 --> 24:51.632
Where are you?

24:54.103 --> 24:57.381
Would you come on?

24:57.406 --> 24:59.550
- [energy surges]
- [shouts, groans]

24:59.575 --> 25:02.453
<i>[tense music]</i>

25:02.478 --> 25:05.122
<i>♪ ♪</i>

25:05.147 --> 25:07.225
[stammering] Hi!

25:07.250 --> 25:09.560
It's okay. He's with us.

25:09.585 --> 25:10.895
- Really?
- Yes, really.

25:10.920 --> 25:12.445
And we have to go right now.

25:12.470 --> 25:13.881
- Where's Three?
- I don't know.

25:13.906 --> 25:15.399
- He was right behind me.
- What?

25:15.424 --> 25:16.467
We have to go back for him.

25:16.492 --> 25:17.668
What are you, nuts?

25:17.693 --> 25:19.337
We're about to be overrun.

25:19.362 --> 25:22.396
[gunfire]

25:23.366 --> 25:25.132
[beeping]

25:28.270 --> 25:30.771
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

25:30.796 --> 25:32.374
All right, now is not the time for

25:32.399 --> 25:34.018
this "all for one"
shit. We're all gonna die

25:34.043 --> 25:37.455
if we don't leave here right now.

25:37.480 --> 25:39.757
Six.

25:39.782 --> 25:42.323
[gunfire]

25:42.348 --> 25:44.147
Go!

25:53.884 --> 25:55.395
Report.

25:55.420 --> 25:57.308
The prisoners have escaped, ma'am.

25:57.333 --> 25:59.010
And the Blink Drive is gone.

25:59.035 --> 26:00.834
Commander Nieman is not gonna be happy.

26:03.072 --> 26:04.104
You're dismissed.

26:07.961 --> 26:10.947
<i>[ominous music]</i>

26:10.972 --> 26:18.010
<i>♪ ♪</i>

26:26.153 --> 26:27.800
I'm detecting something.

26:28.883 --> 26:30.302
It's the Marauder.

26:30.980 --> 26:32.275
Open a channel.

26:33.189 --> 26:35.038
<i>Come in, "Raza." This is the Marauder.</i>

26:35.063 --> 26:36.606
We're reading you. What happened?

26:36.631 --> 26:38.253
Truffault said it was a setup.

26:38.278 --> 26:40.610
<i>Yeah, we ran into a bit of a problem.</i>

26:40.840 --> 26:42.273
Is everyone okay?

26:44.059 --> 26:45.565
Not exactly.

26:49.308 --> 26:52.155
Don't worry. We're
gonna go back for him.

26:52.386 --> 26:53.781
We're gonna need help.

26:54.115 --> 26:55.448
Hey.

26:58.272 --> 27:00.148
You sent us into a trap.

27:00.174 --> 27:01.560
<i>And it was my man who got you out.</i>

27:01.586 --> 27:03.566
- Not all of us.
<i>- I'm sorry about that,</i>

27:03.591 --> 27:04.667
<i>but you were not the only one</i>

27:04.692 --> 27:06.202
<i>who was double-crossed.</i>

27:06.343 --> 27:08.020
We never should've trusted Traugott.

27:08.046 --> 27:09.606
<i>No one expected them to turn.</i>

27:09.976 --> 27:12.647
<i>They've suffered more at the hands
of Ferrous Corp than anyone.</i>

27:13.321 --> 27:15.042
<i>I suppose they figured
it was their only chance</i>

27:15.067 --> 27:16.813
- <i>at survival.</i>
- Well, they figured wrong.

27:16.838 --> 27:18.783
Ferrous Corp is going down.

27:18.916 --> 27:20.748
<i>Well, I appreciate
your confidence, but...</i>

27:20.773 --> 27:24.505
The Aslanov Field is disabled.
The whole network is fried.

27:24.531 --> 27:26.254
They're not bringing
it online any time soon,

27:26.279 --> 27:29.257
which means that base is wide open.

27:29.282 --> 27:31.059
<i>- You're certain of that?</i>
- Yes.

27:31.084 --> 27:32.794
So, Ferrous will be
sending in their ships

27:32.819 --> 27:35.030
as fast as they can to protect it,

27:35.055 --> 27:38.500
but like you said...
they're spread thin.

27:38.525 --> 27:41.436
- We have the advantage.
<i>- Had the advantage.</i>

27:41.461 --> 27:43.572
<i>It wasn't only Traugott that turned.</i>

27:43.597 --> 27:46.474
<i>Electus, Inkosi, and Novina all launched</i>

27:46.499 --> 27:48.443
<i>simultaneous attacks
against our holdings</i>

27:48.468 --> 27:52.213
- <i>across a dozen sectors.</i>
- It doesn't matter.

27:52.238 --> 27:54.115
You take out Ferrous,
and they'll all go running

27:54.140 --> 27:57.586
with their tails between their legs.

27:57.611 --> 27:59.054
<i>I'll have to run this by the board.</i>

27:59.079 --> 28:00.789
The board?

28:00.814 --> 28:03.815
This isn't a corporate
takeover. This is war.

28:06.999 --> 28:09.020
<i>Maybe we can spare a half dozen ships.</i>

28:09.045 --> 28:10.622
- That won't be enough.
<i>- But right now,</i>

28:10.647 --> 28:12.649
<i>it's all I can do.</i>

28:12.674 --> 28:14.469
Well, I might be able to do better.

28:14.494 --> 28:16.594
[screen chirps off]

28:21.801 --> 28:24.836
[door whooshes open]

28:29.542 --> 28:31.686
We need to talk.

28:31.711 --> 28:33.788
What about?

28:33.813 --> 28:36.958
Teku has a fleet. Nine warships...

28:36.983 --> 28:39.076
Loyalists who escaped the coup.

28:39.101 --> 28:40.929
It's not enough to take back the throne,

28:40.954 --> 28:43.031
but it is a good place to start.

28:43.056 --> 28:45.623
- Why are you telling me this?
- There's no point in lying.

28:47.127 --> 28:50.038
We both know I was ready to kill you.

28:50.063 --> 28:52.040
But there's something more
important at stake now.

28:52.065 --> 28:53.575
And what would that be?

28:53.600 --> 28:57.045
First, I need to know.

28:57.070 --> 29:00.081
Did you make an alliance
with Ferrous Corp?

29:00.106 --> 29:02.217
Hardly. It was a one-time arrangement.

29:02.242 --> 29:04.019
Commander Nieman knew I had an interest

29:04.044 --> 29:05.654
in seeing you brought to Zairon.

29:05.679 --> 29:08.023
- In exchange for?
- He wanted me to use

29:08.048 --> 29:11.292
my influence with the League
to prevent a trade embargo.

29:11.317 --> 29:12.650
Why do you care?

29:16.389 --> 29:19.367
If you pledge Teku's fleet to help us,

29:19.392 --> 29:20.869
I'll release you.

29:20.894 --> 29:22.760
Help you do what?

29:25.198 --> 29:28.633
Win this war.

29:33.573 --> 29:35.417
- [groaning]
- Come on.

29:35.442 --> 29:37.108
Wake up.

29:38.778 --> 29:41.056
[grunts]

29:41.081 --> 29:43.124
[grunts, groans]

29:43.149 --> 29:45.193
[sighs] Two. [chuckles]

29:45.218 --> 29:48.997
- What the hell?
- I am not Two.

29:49.022 --> 29:51.099
Ah, shit. Portia.

29:51.124 --> 29:54.636
So, what happened? How
did the others get away?

29:54.661 --> 29:56.979
I didn't know they got away,
but thanks for letting me know.

29:57.004 --> 29:59.441
[scoffs] God, it was Wexler, wasn't it?

29:59.466 --> 30:02.077
- That little weasel.
- Gotta admit,

30:02.102 --> 30:04.136
you kind of screwed him
over on that last deal.

30:04.161 --> 30:05.842
Mm. I know.

30:05.867 --> 30:07.582
Although, I never thought
he'd have the balls

30:07.607 --> 30:08.917
to do anything about it.

30:08.942 --> 30:12.253
God, Nieman is gonna be pissed.

30:12.278 --> 30:14.589
Why are you working
with that snake, anyway?

30:14.614 --> 30:17.959
Because... he's gonna win.

30:17.984 --> 30:20.818
[chuckles] Game's not over yet, honey.

30:24.758 --> 30:27.902
Receiving a signal from the "Raza," sir.

30:27.927 --> 30:29.026
Onscreen.

30:30.830 --> 30:33.475
- Emperor.
- <i>Teku.</i>

30:33.500 --> 30:35.477
<i>I thought I might never see you again.</i>

30:35.502 --> 30:37.479
I have a fleet at your disposal, Heika.

30:37.504 --> 30:40.448
And there are many more
like us back on Zairon.

30:40.473 --> 30:42.650
<i>Men and women who remain loyal,</i>

30:42.675 --> 30:44.719
<i>and will fight to see
their emperor restored</i>

30:44.744 --> 30:47.122
- <i>to his rightful place.</i>
- There may come a time

30:47.147 --> 30:48.957
for that one day, but not right now.

30:48.982 --> 30:52.227
First, we're going to
secure a powerful ally.

30:52.252 --> 30:54.662
The Mikkei Combine has an opportunity

30:54.687 --> 30:57.031
<i>to deliver Ferrous Corp a death blow.</i>

30:57.056 --> 30:59.667
- <i>We are going to help them do it.</i>
- As I said,

30:59.692 --> 31:01.336
the fleet is at your command.

31:01.361 --> 31:03.138
<i>We'll send you the coordinates.</i>

31:03.163 --> 31:05.196
- <i>Prepare for battle.</i>
- Yes, Heika.

31:08.368 --> 31:10.712
You know, I would be more useful

31:10.737 --> 31:13.047
- at the command of my ships.
- Nice try,

31:13.072 --> 31:16.115
but I won't be letting you go
until after we win the battle.

31:17.977 --> 31:21.022
Android, signal Commander Truffault.

31:21.047 --> 31:22.557
It's on.

31:22.582 --> 31:25.616
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

31:30.690 --> 31:32.867
Mmm! Let me tell you something.

31:32.892 --> 31:35.236
Your Android may be a
few neural pathways short

31:35.261 --> 31:38.239
of a full deck, but she sure can cook.

31:38.264 --> 31:40.441
All right. The latest
Mikkei intelligence

31:40.466 --> 31:41.810
says that Ferrous has somewhere between

31:41.835 --> 31:43.812
10 to 15 ships already on-site.

31:43.837 --> 31:45.353
So the odds are just about even.

31:45.378 --> 31:48.416
Well, you better believe
they got more on the way.

31:48.441 --> 31:50.552
When we drop out, things
are gonna happen fast.

31:50.577 --> 31:52.153
I want you backing up
the Android on weapons,

31:52.178 --> 31:53.488
and you on shields.

31:53.513 --> 31:55.423
Power management is gonna be key.

31:55.448 --> 31:57.525
- What do you want me to do?
- I should probably just

31:57.550 --> 31:59.427
- lock you up.
- You do recall who saved who,

31:59.452 --> 32:01.129
- right?
- [sighs] Yes.

32:01.154 --> 32:02.430
Fine. Next to me,

32:02.455 --> 32:04.069
keeping your mouth shut.

32:04.094 --> 32:05.303
[pops lips]

32:05.328 --> 32:08.236
- What about Three?
- Well, the goal is

32:08.261 --> 32:10.038
to disable the Ferrous fleet.

32:10.063 --> 32:12.173
Once we've done that,
we can board the station

32:12.198 --> 32:14.008
- and get him out.
- Really?

32:14.033 --> 32:16.010
- That's your plan?
- Didn't we just say

32:16.035 --> 32:17.458
that you would keep your mouth shut?

32:17.483 --> 32:19.194
Yeah, on the bridge,
during the battle, sure,

32:19.219 --> 32:21.082
but we're not there yet. I'm
just a little bit concerned

32:21.107 --> 32:22.633
that you have conflicting goals, here.

32:22.658 --> 32:23.969
Do you wanna win the battle

32:23.994 --> 32:25.338
or save your friend?

32:25.363 --> 32:28.122
<i>[tense music]</i>

32:28.147 --> 32:34.696
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:34.721 --> 32:37.665
<i>[musical sting]</i>

32:37.690 --> 32:40.101
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

32:40.126 --> 32:43.928
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:50.490 --> 32:52.918
<i>Mikkei should be arriving as planned.</i>

32:53.162 --> 32:54.868
We're approaching the coordinates.

32:54.893 --> 32:56.678
Mikkei has engaged the shipyard.

32:56.703 --> 32:58.605
Ready shields. Prepare to open fire.

32:58.630 --> 33:00.807
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

33:00.832 --> 33:03.132
[engines whooshing]

33:11.843 --> 33:13.042
Fire, now!

33:21.720 --> 33:23.396
[shouting]

33:23.421 --> 33:25.699
- [electricity crackling]
- Evasive maneuvers.

33:25.724 --> 33:26.733
[electricity hissing]

33:26.758 --> 33:28.435
[grunts]

33:28.460 --> 33:29.492
Fire again!

33:37.502 --> 33:38.701
Let's go.

33:41.373 --> 33:44.351
[ship rumbling]

33:44.376 --> 33:46.519
- What's going on?
- Well, these forward sections

33:46.544 --> 33:48.855
- are no longer safe.
- [sighs]

33:48.880 --> 33:50.757
Whoa.

33:50.782 --> 33:52.382
What do we have here?

33:54.386 --> 33:57.130
A combined fleet of
Mikkei and Ishida ships

33:57.155 --> 34:00.367
- just launched an attack.
- Ishida?

34:00.392 --> 34:01.591
You gotta be kidding me.

34:04.863 --> 34:07.897
[metal squealing]

34:09.402 --> 34:10.543
Whoa.

34:10.568 --> 34:12.545
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

34:12.570 --> 34:14.547
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:14.572 --> 34:16.983
Oh, shit.

34:17.007 --> 34:18.184
Whoa, whoa, whoa!

34:18.208 --> 34:19.953
[shouts, grunts]

34:19.978 --> 34:22.422
- [pants]
- Maybe we should leave.

34:22.447 --> 34:24.547
You think?

34:27.185 --> 34:28.928
No.

34:28.953 --> 34:31.902
[explosions, electricity crackling]

34:31.928 --> 34:33.366
Shields are down to 50%

34:33.391 --> 34:34.967
and I don't have any
more power reserves.

34:34.993 --> 34:36.936
Two of the Ishida cruisers
have been destroyed.

34:36.960 --> 34:38.721
This isn't working.
We can't break through.

34:39.730 --> 34:41.341
Can you remote pilot the Marauder,

34:41.366 --> 34:43.109
- get it closer to the shipyard?
- Of course.

34:43.134 --> 34:44.744
What good will that do?

34:44.768 --> 34:46.478
We'll rig the Blink
Drive to go critical.

34:46.504 --> 34:48.481
It'll tear a hole in space-time
big enough to take out

34:48.505 --> 34:50.750
- the entire facility.
- Will that work?

34:50.775 --> 34:52.318
- It's possible.
- But we have to

34:52.342 --> 34:54.654
- get Three off first.
- Sensors indicate

34:54.679 --> 34:56.822
several of the docked
Ferrous ships are powering up.

34:56.848 --> 34:59.159
They're preparing to launch.

34:59.184 --> 35:01.995
I'm sorry, but I don't think
we'll get another chance.

35:02.020 --> 35:04.364
Wait a minute. I'm receiving a signal.

35:04.389 --> 35:06.232
- Audio only.
- <i>Hey, guys.</i>

35:06.257 --> 35:07.934
- <i>How's it going out there?</i>
- Three?

35:07.959 --> 35:09.936
<i>Yup, yeah, it's me. Just wanted to</i>

35:09.961 --> 35:11.738
<i>let you know that I'm
hitching a ride out of here.</i>

35:11.763 --> 35:13.907
With who?

35:13.932 --> 35:16.342
You are not gonna believe it.

35:16.367 --> 35:18.668
Portia Lin.

35:20.305 --> 35:22.182
She's got her faults,
but a willingness to die

35:22.207 --> 35:24.317
for someone else's
cause ain't one of them.

35:24.342 --> 35:26.451
<i>Guess you could say we
have that in common.</i>

35:26.476 --> 35:28.221
I don't really know where we're going,

35:28.246 --> 35:30.323
but... ah, what the hell.

35:30.348 --> 35:32.025
<i>Anywhere's better than here, huh?</i>

35:32.050 --> 35:33.660
Wait a minute. How will we find you?

35:33.685 --> 35:35.717
- <i>[electronic chirp]</i>
- Three?

35:35.742 --> 35:37.453
The signal has been terminated.

35:37.478 --> 35:39.232
That's it, then. There's
nothing stopping us now.

35:39.257 --> 35:41.139
I'll go prep the drive.

35:41.164 --> 35:42.441
Two?

35:42.466 --> 35:44.128
I'm sorry, but I don't believe

35:44.153 --> 35:46.906
you have the technical
expertise required.

35:46.931 --> 35:50.143
Of course. [stammers]
I could use your help.

35:50.168 --> 35:51.778
But... this battle isn't over yet.

35:51.803 --> 35:53.146
- You're needed here.
- Hey, what am I?

35:53.171 --> 35:54.647
Chopped liver? I mean, I know

35:54.672 --> 35:56.567
I'm not to be trusted, but
you gotta at least believe

35:56.592 --> 35:57.984
I don't wanna die out here.

35:58.009 --> 35:59.686
- I can handle navigation.
- [electricity crackles]

35:59.711 --> 36:02.388
[shouts, groans]

36:02.413 --> 36:04.457
Yeah, all right. Buy us as much time

36:04.482 --> 36:06.783
as you can. Let's go.

36:11.856 --> 36:13.535
All right, what am I looking at here?

36:13.560 --> 36:18.404
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:18.429 --> 36:20.607
Wait. We've got a problem.

36:20.632 --> 36:22.242
What is it?

36:22.267 --> 36:24.300
[circuitry surging, powering down]

36:30.708 --> 36:33.720
<i>[musical sting]</i>

36:33.745 --> 36:36.055
Why?

36:36.080 --> 36:38.281
This is the beginning of a new age.

36:39.384 --> 36:40.827
[gunshot]

36:40.852 --> 36:43.753
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

36:49.193 --> 36:51.061
[grunts, sighs]

36:54.353 --> 36:56.830
<i>Bridge, this is Two.
I've prepped the drive,</i>

36:56.855 --> 36:59.491
<i>but we've got a problem.
The Android is down.</i>

37:01.727 --> 37:03.537
- What happened?
- There was an overload

37:03.562 --> 37:04.972
in the relay. She was standing

37:04.997 --> 37:06.974
right next to it. She's self-repairing,

37:06.999 --> 37:09.411
<i>but we've got no one to
remote-pilot the Marauder.</i>

37:12.965 --> 37:14.268
I'm on my way.

37:14.730 --> 37:16.045
No!

37:17.067 --> 37:19.586
No, there's no way I'm
letting you do this.

37:19.611 --> 37:21.774
If we lose this battle, we lose the war.

37:22.815 --> 37:26.160
So what? Who cares who comes out on top?

37:26.185 --> 37:28.362
Ferrous Corp, the GA, some other corp...

37:28.387 --> 37:30.435
- It's all the same.
- How can you say that?

37:30.460 --> 37:31.965
After everything Ferrous Corp has done,

37:31.990 --> 37:33.380
all the lives they've taken...

37:33.405 --> 37:36.050
The countless more they'll
take if we don't stop them now.

37:36.075 --> 37:38.108
Your life isn't worth it.

37:40.899 --> 37:42.543
It's not worth it to me.

37:42.568 --> 37:46.182
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37:46.207 --> 37:48.415
Since Hyperion-8, all
I've been talking about

37:48.440 --> 37:50.584
is wanting to make a difference.

37:50.609 --> 37:52.186
Here's my chance.

37:52.211 --> 37:55.055
- I can't look away.
- I don't wanna lose you.

37:55.080 --> 37:57.057
[breathing shakily]

37:57.082 --> 38:00.427
Don't go... please!

38:00.452 --> 38:02.963
[crying]

38:02.988 --> 38:03.964
[whispers] I have to.

38:03.989 --> 38:06.100
[boom]

38:06.125 --> 38:07.367
[electricity crackles]

38:07.392 --> 38:08.770
Uh, sorry to interrupt,

38:08.795 --> 38:10.164
but I could use a little help.

38:10.189 --> 38:11.663
The aft shields are about to fail.

38:14.600 --> 38:17.067
I'm sorry.

38:45.951 --> 38:47.395
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

38:47.420 --> 38:49.179
All right, I'm heading in.

38:55.741 --> 38:58.275
[engines whooshing]

39:03.982 --> 39:05.626
Oh, boy.

39:05.651 --> 39:07.861
Three more Ferrous ships
just dropped out of FTL.

39:07.886 --> 39:10.731
If he's gonna do this
thing, he's gotta do it now.

39:10.756 --> 39:13.734
[computer beeping]

39:13.759 --> 39:15.769
<i>[mysterious music]</i>

39:15.794 --> 39:17.871
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:17.896 --> 39:20.931
[Android beeping quietly]

39:23.850 --> 39:25.395
[beeping]

39:25.420 --> 39:27.247
_

39:27.272 --> 39:28.682
What?

39:28.707 --> 39:30.317
- What is it?
- The Android...

39:30.342 --> 39:33.387
Her body's offline, but
her mind is still linked.

39:33.412 --> 39:35.455
_

39:35.480 --> 39:38.200
_

39:38.984 --> 39:40.417
Oh, shit.

39:42.387 --> 39:44.398
- [comm beeps]
- Two, where are you?

39:44.423 --> 39:46.456
<i>I'm on my way back to the bridge.</i>

39:48.360 --> 39:49.903
[static]

39:49.928 --> 39:51.432
Six, are you there?

39:51.457 --> 39:53.068
Marauder, come in.

39:53.093 --> 39:55.142
Six, do you read?

39:55.167 --> 39:56.376
[faltering static]

39:56.401 --> 39:57.834
[sighs]

40:04.009 --> 40:06.019
<i>- Ryo?</i>
- Yes, Five.

40:06.044 --> 40:07.654
<i>We need your help.</i>

40:07.679 --> 40:10.247
[inhales, exhales deeply]

40:15.254 --> 40:18.288
[door whooshing]

40:19.691 --> 40:21.391
Five, what's going on?

40:22.594 --> 40:24.728
<i>[musical sting]</i>

40:27.266 --> 40:29.209
What are you doing out here?

40:29.234 --> 40:31.311
Keeping my word.

40:31.336 --> 40:33.146
[energy surges]

40:33.171 --> 40:36.116
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

40:36.141 --> 40:39.353
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:39.378 --> 40:41.601
I repeat, it's a trap.

40:41.626 --> 40:43.971
Six, are you there? Please respond.

40:43.996 --> 40:45.440
<i>[garbled signal] I repeat, it's a...</i>

40:45.465 --> 40:46.994
"Raza," is that you?

40:47.019 --> 40:48.184
<i>[static] I...</i>

40:49.721 --> 40:51.899
I think Two's been infected
by one of those aliens.

40:51.924 --> 40:53.934
This whole thing was her idea.

40:53.959 --> 40:57.237
Whatever you do, don't
activate the drive.

40:57.262 --> 40:59.083
Six, please respond!

40:59.108 --> 41:00.986
I'm telling you, it's all the radiation

41:01.011 --> 41:03.889
from those damaged ships.
You're not getting through.

41:03.914 --> 41:05.779
Raza, I don't know if
you're reading this...

41:05.804 --> 41:06.880
<i>[static]</i>

41:06.905 --> 41:08.515
But I'm in position.

41:08.540 --> 41:11.007
[beeping, whirring]

41:12.244 --> 41:13.854
Activating the drive.

41:13.879 --> 41:16.823
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

41:16.848 --> 41:18.415
Bye.

41:23.588 --> 41:26.623
[energy exploding]

41:34.788 --> 41:37.633
<i>[intense music]</i>

41:37.658 --> 41:39.646
- What happened?
- Okay, I'm getting

41:39.671 --> 41:41.482
some seriously strange readings here.

41:41.507 --> 41:43.318
It's a massive space-time anomaly.

41:43.530 --> 41:46.268
One thing's for sure:
the shipyard's gone.

41:46.416 --> 41:47.976
I guess it wasn't a trick after all.

41:48.002 --> 41:49.222
Wait, something's happening.

41:49.247 --> 41:51.024
Energy readings are off the charts.

41:51.049 --> 41:54.094
[energy surging]

41:54.119 --> 42:00.300
<i>♪ ♪</i>

42:00.325 --> 42:02.798
Something's coming through.

42:03.135 --> 42:06.413
Whatever it is... it's big.

42:12.237 --> 42:15.071
Oh, my God...

42:18.918 --> 42:20.060
What?

42:20.412 --> 42:21.801
What is it?

42:23.982 --> 42:27.017
[energy surging]

42:36.655 --> 42:38.584
The black ships.

42:38.892 --> 42:41.287
<i>[intense music]</i>

42:45.070 --> 42:48.802
